{
  "texts": [
    "In a telecom network where multiple systems are continuously monitored, excessive false positives can overwhelm operational teams, leading to alert fatigue and desensitization to genuine alerts.",
    "By ensuring that anomaly detection models achieve high precision, telecom operators can focus their resources on investigating and resolving actual issues rather than wasting time on false alarms.",
    "This targeted approach not only optimizes resource allocation but also enhances overall network reliability.",
    "Recall is equally critical, as it measures the system's ability to capture all actual anomalies present in the network.",
    "A low recall rate can result in undetected anomalies, which may escalate into service outages or security breaches, negatively impacting customer trust and satisfaction."
  ]
}